column4: "dougmck@pipeline.com.au. See 'The Jazz Theory Book'by Mark Levine (Sher Music)  p 375\012"
"or Band-in-a-box file for chords He plays this on his Maybeck Hall CD (Concord Jazz CCD-4466)\012"
"The whole song basically uses simple triads over a G pedal the whole way through "
"The LH keeps an insistent G pedal - often in octaves - thru the whole song"
"Most of the RH stuff is based on the notes of the triad with diatonic neighbouring tones "
"Based on A magor Triad  with a missing note in each group of three"
"On the A/G chord the A triad is inverted"
"4 note Perfect Fourths from the C Major scale"
"'Country' sounding lick with the 9th (=2nd) sounded with the 3rd"
"Scale fragment from Eb Maj Sacle on Gsusb9 which is sometimes called the Phrygian chord"
